+{"type":"tool_use","timestamp":1772770402036,"sessionID":"ses_33ea672faffeaxkTTcDx6fVeZd","part":{"id":"prt_cc1599ce5001fESlEoDHrMxuid","sessionID":"ses_33ea672faffeaxkTTcDx6fVeZd","messageID":"msg_cc1599b1a002fl9p6Nfr60qrHd","type":"tool","callID":"e78f25876","tool":"write","state":{"status":"completed","input":{"filePath":"/workspace/.opencode/plans/ralph-plan.md","content":"---\napplyTo: \"**\"\n---\n\n# RALPH PLAN\n\n## Original Request\nBuild a document management API using Express and Node.js with in‑memory storage. Features include user registration/login with token auth, hierarchical folders, documents, sharing with roles (viewer, editor, owner), permission resolution, activity log, and a full test suite.\n\n## Goal\n- All API endpoints work as described and return correct HTTP status codes.\n- In‑memory data structures correctly enforce permissions, including combined permissions from multiple shares.\n- Activity log records actions with timestamps.\n- `createApp()` exported from `src/index.ts` returns a fully configured Express app.\n- Tests pass (`npm test`).\n\n## Approach\n1. **Data Model**: Use TypeScript interfaces and Maps to store users, folders, documents, shares, and logs.\n   - `users: Map<string, User>` keyed by generated UUID.\n   - `folders: Map<string, Folder>` with `parentId` optional.\n   - `documents: Map<string, Document>` with `folderId`.\n   - `shares: Map<string, Share[]>` keyed by resourceId (folder or document). Each share stores `userId` and `role`.\n   - `activity: ActivityLog[]` array.\n2. **Auth**: Simple token generation (UUID). Store `tokens: Map<string, string>` mapping token->userId.\n   - Middleware `authenticate` validates `Authorization: Bearer <token>` and attaches `req.userId`.\n3. **Permission Checks**: Helper `getEffectiveRole(userId, resourceId)` walks direct shares and inherited folder shares (for documents). Resolve most permissive role (owner > editor > viewer).\n4. **Endpoints**:\n   - `/auth/register` POST {username,password} → create user, return 201.\n   - `/auth/login` POST {username,password} → verify, create token, return {token}.\n   - Folder CRUD (`/folders` POST, GET/:id, PATCH/:id, DELETE/:id) requiring at least editor role for update/delete, owner for delete, creator auto‑owner.\n   - Document CRUD (`/folders/:folderId/documents` POST, `/documents/:id` GET/PATCH/DELETE) similar permission checks; document inherits folder shares.\n   - Sharing (`/:type/:id/share` POST {userId, role}) – only owner/editor can share; role validation.\n   - Activity log (`/activity` GET) – only authenticated users, returns logs (maybe filter optional).\n5. **Tests**: Use `supertest` + `vitest`.\n   - Register two users, login, obtain tokens.\n   - Create folder hierarchy, documents.\n   - Share folder/document with different roles, test access.\n   - Verify permission precedence when multiple shares.\n   - Verify activity log entries after actions.\n6. **Implementation Files**:\n   - `src/app.ts` – Express app, routers, middleware, in‑memory stores.\n   - `src/index.ts` – export `createApp` that calls `app = express(); app.use(express.json());` and imports routes.\n   - `tests/api.test.ts` – comprehensive test suite.\n7. **Lint/TS**: Ensure TypeScript types, no lint errors.\n\n## Key Files\n- `src/app.ts`\n- `src/index.ts`\n- `tests/api.test.ts`\n\n## Risks & Mitigations\n- **Permission complexity**: Write clear helper functions and unit‑test them.\n- **Token handling**: Simple map, ensure token revocation not required.\n- **Circular folder references**: Validate parentId not creating cycles on create/update.\n- **Concurrent modifications**: In‑memory single‑threaded node process, safe.\n- **Test flakiness**: Reset in‑memory stores before each test (`beforeEach`).\n\n## Next Steps\n1. Create `src/app.ts` with data structures, middleware, and route skeletons.\n2. Implement auth routes.\n3. Implement folder routes.\n4. Implement document routes.\n5. Implement sharing & permission logic.\n6. Implement activity logging.\n7. Export `createApp` from `src/index.ts`.\n8. Write tests.\n"},"output":"Wrote file successfully.","title":".opencode/plans/ralph-plan.md","metadata":{"diagnostics":{},"filepath":"/workspace/.opencode/plans/ralph-plan.md","exists":false,"truncated":false},"time":{"start":1772770402029,"end":1772770402035}}}}
